      },
      "id": 15,
      "options": {
        "content": "<div style=\"line-height:1.7;font-size:13px;\"><strong>Data sources:</strong> Most market, FX, macro, credit, liquidity, reserve, and cross-border proxy series come from FRED via the St. Louis Fed. The supply-chain panel uses the Federal Reserve Bank of New York's official GSCPI CSV. <strong>Axis note:</strong> snapshot tables show absolute levels. Trend panels use absolute source units when the series are comparable, such as rates, oil, liquidity, and flow proxies; cross-region equity, FX, and reserve comparison panels use percentage change from the visible range start because their absolute levels are not comparable. <strong>What this dashboard can show well today:</strong> global equity benchmarks, major FX, commodities, rates, credit stress, reserve buffers, and rough cross-border flow proxies. <strong>What is still missing:</strong> true global multi-asset fund-flow coverage and central-bank gold holdings by country are not yet wired into the live sync. The gold-reserve source has been identified, but its download path is gated by terms and needs a cleaner ingestion path before I would trust it in production. <strong>Refresh cadence:</strong> server-side sync every 10 minutes.</div>",
        "mode": "html"
      },
